<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-92-0067 </DOCNO><TEXT>Major changes in the global climate are virtually certain by the mid-21stcentury due to the carbon dioxide and other greenhouse gases. Researchersare beginning to explore ways we can adopt. Scientist have long knownthat human activities, particularly the burning of fossil fuels, areartificially increasing the volume of greenhouse gases in the earth'satmosphere. This increase will eventually make the planet the hottestit has been in history. What remains controversial about the greenhouseeffect is the rate of this global warming, its regional distribution,and most of all, what to do about the problem.</TEXT></DOC>